(768, 418, NULL, 'SEAT BELTS', 19149, 'Volvo Car USA, LLC (Volvo Car) is recalling certain 2021 XC40, XC 40 Recharge, V60CC, V90, V90CC, XC90, and 2021-2022 V60, XC60, S60 vehicles.  The seat belt automatic locking retractors may deactivate early, which can prevent the child restraint system from securing properly.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 208, \"Occupant Crash Protection.\" ', 'An unsecured child restraint system can increase the risk of injury during a crash. ', 'Dealers will inspect and replace the seat belt assemblies, as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed October 13, 2021.  Owners may contact Volvo Car customer service at 1-888-458-1552.  Volvo Car\'s number for this recall is R10111. '),
