(1858, 433, NULL, 'STEERING:RACK AND PINION', 22462, 'Toyota Motor Engineering & Manufacturing (Toyota) is recalling certain 2008-2022 Sequoia and 2007-2021 Tundra vehicles.  The power steering gear assembly may have been manufactured incorrectly, which can result in an oil leak. ', 'An oil leak may cause a sudden loss of power steering assist, increasing the risk of a crash. ', 'Dealers will inspect and replace the power steering gear assembly as necessary, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed on January 21, 2022.  Owners may contact Toyota customer service at 1-800-331-4331.  Toyota\'s numbers for this recall are 21TB10 and 21TA10. '),
