(2215, 677, NULL, 'SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:FLUID', 4177, 'Harley-Davidson Motor Company (Harley-Davidson) is recalling certain 2021-2022 XL1200X, XL883N, and 2021 XL1200NS XL Sportster motorcycles.  The brake fluid warning labels may detach from the brake fluid reservoir caps.  As such, these motorcycles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 122, \"Motorcycle Brake Systems.\" ', 'Missing brake fluid warning labels may lead to improper brake system maintenance, affecting brake performance and increasing the risk of a crash. ', 'Harley-Davidson will mail replacement labels to owners, free of charge.  Owners may also take their motorcycles to a dealer for label inspection and replacement, free of charge.  Owner notification letters were mailed April 4, 2022.  Harley\'s number for this recall is 0632.'),
