(2879, 872, NULL, 'ENGINE AND ENGINE COOLING:EXHAUST SYSTEM', 1072, 'Ducati North America (Ducati) is recalling certain 2018-2021 Scrambler 1100 motorcycles.  The exhaust valve cable could contact the main positive battery wire and potentially short-circuit.', 'An electrical short-circuit increases the risk of fire.', 'Ducati will notify owners, and dealers will install a new cable guide and self-locking cable tie to the exhaust valve cable, free of charge.  The recall began January 22, 2021.  Owners may contact Ducati customer service at 1-888-391-5446.  Ducati\'s number for this recall is SRV-RCL-20-003.'),
(2880, 872, NULL, 'ELECTRICAL SYSTEM:12V/24V/48V BATTERY:CABLES', 1072, 'Ducati North America (Ducati) is recalling certain 2018-2021 Scrambler 1100 motorcycles.  The exhaust valve cable could contact the main positive battery wire and potentially short-circuit.', 'An electrical short-circuit increases the risk of fire.', 'Ducati will notify owners, and dealers will install a new cable guide and self-locking cable tie to the exhaust valve cable, free of charge.  The recall began January 22, 2021.  Owners may contact Ducati customer service at 1-888-391-5446.  Ducati\'s number for this recall is SRV-RCL-20-003.'),
(2881, 873, NULL, 'SERVICE BRAKES, AIR', 28, 'Daimler Trucks North America, LLC (DTNA) is recalling certain 2021 Thomas Built Saf-T-Liner C2 Jouley electric school buses.  If the service brake pedal is pressed and then released while the parking brake is engaged, the parking brake may release unexpectedly.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 121, \"Air Brake Systems.\"', 'An unexpected disengagement of the parking brake without continual application of the service brake may allow the vehicle to roll freely, increasing the risk of a vehicle crash.', 'DTNA will notify owners, and dealers will update the electronic control unit (ECU) software, free of charge.  The recall began January 22, 2021.  Owners may contact DTNA customer service at 1-800-745-8000.  DTNA\'s number for this recall is FL-870.'),
