(2946, 897, NULL, 'EQUIPMENT:MECHANICAL', 694, 'PJ Trailers is recalling certain 2020-2021 DE trailers.  The attachment bolts of the hydraulic cylinder may fail if the hydraulic system is used to lower the dump box once the dump box is already in the fully lowered position. ', 'Use of the dump box after the attachment bolts fail may result in a sudden drop of the box as it is being raised, increasing the risk of injury.', 'PJ Trailers will notify owners, and dealers will replace the hydraulic power unit and the attachment bolts, free of charge.  The recall began October 2, 2020.  Owners may contact PJ Trailers customer service at 1-866-752-8781.'),
(2947, 898, NULL, 'SUSPENSION:MULTIPLE AXLE', 103, 'Daimler Truckers North America LLC (DTNA) is recalling certain 2020-2021 Freightliner 114SD, 122SD and Western Star 4700, and 4900 vehicles equipped with certain SL2065 steerable lift axles.  The lower rear pivot cap screws may not be long enough to sufficiently engage the locking feature of the corresponding nuts.', 'If the screws are not long enough to engage the corresponding nuts, the hardware may separate from the suspension system, becoming a road hazard, increasing the risk of a crash and/or injury. ', 'DTNA will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the lower rear pivot cap screws for the proper length, correcting the hardware as necessary, free of charge.  The recall began October 30, 2020.  Owners may contact DTNA customer service at 1-800-547-0712.  DTNA\'s number for this recall is FL-862.'),
